        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 20 at 5:06PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 505 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Gaylesville to Cherokee Rock Village.
Movement was south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hokes Bluff, Centre, Cedar Bluff, Forney, Centre Municipal Airport,
Leesburg, Sand Rock, Gaylesville, Tennala, Tabor Road, Cherokee Rock
Village, Pleasant Gap, Cornwall Furnace Park, Eastern Weiss Lake,
Ballplay, Slackland, Western Weiss Lake, Moshat, Ball Flat, and
Coloma.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
